snippet.textDisplay: My brother, Chris, would be 43 years old today.... And this story of this lady's reminds me of my own... My brother passed away in 2006 and one of the first things I SPECIFICALLY asked for of his was his Eagle Skull ring.... A silver ring in the shape of a bird skull... Anyway, I wore it all the time and on a college field trip, it was stolen from me... I was so heartbroken... 3 years later we found it, being sold at a flea market, it was the same one because it was not only a uniquely made ring for my brother, but all the bangs, knicks and cuts on it from his accident made it identifiable. We had to buy it off the lady, but I didnt care, I was happy to have it back (she said she bought it off someone who needed the money).... Anyway, long story short.... If the things we lose manage to find our way back to us, then it was always meant to be yours! Congratz on finding your ring! I know it was special!

My brother passed away in 2006 and one of the first things I SPECIFICALLY asked for of his was his Eagle Skull ring.... A silver ring in the shape of a bird skull... Anyway, I wore it all the time and on a college field trip, it was stolen from me... I was so heartbroken... 3 years later we found it, being sold at a flea market, it was the same one because it was not only a uniquely made ring for my brother, but all the bangs, knicks and cuts on it from his accident made it identifiable. We had to buy it off the lady, but I didnt care, I was happy to have it back (she said she bought it off someone who needed the money).... Anyway, long story short.... If the things we lose manage to find our way back to us, then it was always meant to be yours! Congratz on finding your ring! I know it was special!
